The paper discusses the challenges and need for a discipline on "AI Engineering" to address the reliability, repeatability, trust, and maintainability of AI applications. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper discusses the need for systematic ways of approaching AI software development and certification, which aligns with the sub-categories of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also mentions the use of AI in mission-critical or safety-critical applications, which suggests the sub-category of cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper discusses concerns about the reliability of AI applications, which could also fall under the sub-category of cs.CR (Cryptography and Security).
